In 2003, a philosopher named Thomas Metzinger gave a talk at the University of California.
It aired quietly on a small academic channel — UCTV — and then disappeared from the mainstream completely.
Not censored…
but buried under the weight of ideas too dangerous for public consumption.

If you’ve ever felt like reality has seams… or that the “you” inside your mind might not be who you think — this is for you.

🔔 Subscribe for more mind-bending explorations of reality.
🧠 This episode is based on rare excerpts and archived material from UCTV and Metzinger’s original lectures.

This work is powered by those who resonate with it. - https://buymeacoffee.com/videoadvice
Thank you for being part of the journey.
